Latitude":"41.305670999999997","Longitude":"-72.365979999999993","Narrative":"COMMENT FOR REFILING WITH AMENDED CAUSE CODE - ALSO ADVISED FRA BY PHONE PRIOR TO FILING. FOLLOWINGTHE 5/20, 2016 DERAILMENT OF RAIL CAR NO. NAHX 93375 IN OLD SAYBROOK, CT, P&W OPENED AN INVESTIGATION INTO THE INCIDENT TO DETERMINE ITS CAUSE IN COOPERATION WITH REPRESENTATIVES FROM BOTH AMTRAK ANDTHE FEDERAL RAILROAD ADMINISTRATION (“FRA”). P&W’S MANAGEMENT TEAM CHARGED WITH CONDUCTING THE INVESTIGATION HAD A COMBINED 76 YEARS OF EXPERIENCE IN THE RAILROAD INDUSTRY AND WAS INTIMATELY FAMILIARWITH OPERATING RULES, TRAIN HANDLING PRACTICES, AND RAILCAR MECHANICS. IN P&W’S EXPERT OPINION, ANDIN LIGHT OF THE INFORMATION COLLECTED DURING THE INVESTIGATION, NO SPECIFIC CAUSE COULD BE IDENTIFIED. FOLLOWING DISCUSSIONS WITH AMTRAK AND THE FRA, HOWEVER, A DETERMINATION WAS MADE TO AMEND THE ORIGINAL FILING TO DESIGNATE THE INCIDENT WITH AN “H” (HUMAN FACTOR) CAUSE CODE. THIS DETERMINATION WASMADE IN SPITE OF THE CREW STATEMENTS TAKEN AT THE SCENE, COUPLED WITH MANAGEMENT’S FOLLOW-UP ANALYSIS OF THE CREW’S PERFORMANCE (AND A JOINT INSPECTION OF THE MECHANICAL CONDITION OF THE RAILCAR), WHICH DEMONSTRATED THAT PROPER RULES AND PROCEDURES WERE FOLLOWED AND THAT THE RAILCAR’S BRAKING APPARATUSES FUNCTIONED PROPERLY. IMPORTANTLY, REPRESENTATIVES FROM THE FRA CONDUCTED SEPARATE INTERVIEWSOF P&W’S CREW MEMBERS AS PART OF THEIR INVESTIGATION INTO THE CAUSE.  (CONTINUED - COMPLETE NARRATIVE  ATTCHED)","Joint Track Type":"Main","Joint Track Class":"4","Class Code":"Cl","Class":"Cl","Joint CD":"2","Incident Key":"ATK142489201605","Report Key":"PW160503201605","Reporting Railroad Company Grouping":"Shortline","Reporting Railroad Class":"Class 3","Reporting Railroad SMT Grouping":"SMT-2 - Short Line East","Reporting Parent Railroad Company Code":"PW","Reporting Parent Railroad Company Name":"Providence & Worcester Railroad Company","Reporting Railroad Holding Company":"Genesee & Wyoming","Other Railroad Company